content.description: Start on two smallish crimps, one just under the arete and the obvious one out of the roof for the right hand. Put a heel/toe out and left and do a bump move to a pocket and up to the tip of the prow and topout.
content.protection: Two pads, the lading is built up with logs and they are important to have for a good landing. That being said you still don't want to fall off the easy top.
content.location: Uphill from the bench alongside the access road, and downhill from the overlook parking.

content.description: Walk down the access road (Old State Park road) from the lookout parking area. Down the hill you will see a bench and a trail walking past it, take the trail 70 yards uphill and you will see the obvious overhanging boulder right next to the trail.
